==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monotone
<hw>Mon"o*tone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Monotonous</er>, <er>Monotony</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A single unvaried tone or sound.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The utterance of successive
syllables, words, or sentences, on one unvaried key or line of
pitch.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monotonical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Monotonic</ent>⟦br⟧
